{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":667,"text":"So, well, I do applied math,"},{"time":2770,"text":"and this is a peculiar problem"},{"time":4294,"text":"for anyone who does applied math, is that"},{"time":6467,"text":"we are like management consultants."},{"time":8400,"text":"No one knows what the hell we do."},{"time":10346,"text":"So I am going to give you some -- attempt today"},{"time":12620,"text":"to try and explain to you what I do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":14913,"text":"So, dancing is one of the most human of activities."},{"time":18234,"text":"We delight at ballet virtuosos and tap dancers"},{"time":21916,"text":"you will see later on."},{"time":23064,"text":"Now, ballet requires an extraordinary level of expertise"},{"time":25754,"text":"and a high level of skill,"},{"time":28668,"text":"and probably a level of initial suitability"},{"time":31199,"text":"that may well have a genetic component to it."},{"time":33046,"text":"Now, sadly, neurological disorders such as Parkinson's disease"},{"time":36439,"text":"gradually destroy this extraordinary ability,"},{"time":38526,"text":"as it is doing to my friend Jan Stripling, who was"},{"time":40849,"text":"a virtuoso ballet dancer in his time."},{"time":43816,"text":"So great progress and treatment has been made over the years."},{"time":46870,"text":"However, there are 6.3 million people worldwide"},{"time":49814,"text":"who have the disease, and they have to live with"},{"time":53262,"text":"incurable weakness, tremor, rigidity"},{"time":55830,"text":"and the other symptoms that go along with the disease,"},{"time":57687,"text":"so what we need are objective tools"},{"time":60070,"text":"to detect the disease before it's too late."},{"time":63127,"text":"We need to be able to measure progression objectively,"},{"time":65681,"text":"and ultimately, the only way we're going to know"},{"time":68854,"text":"when we actually have a cure is when we have"},{"time":71046,"text":"an objective measure that can answer that for sure."}]},{"cues":[{"time":74444,"text":"But frustratingly, with Parkinson's disease"},{"time":77294,"text":"and other movement disorders, there are no biomarkers,"},{"time":79647,"text":"so there's no simple blood test that you can do,"},{"time":81876,"text":"and the best that we have is like"},{"time":83678,"text":"this 20-minute neurologist test."},{"time":85919,"text":"You have to go to the clinic to do it. It's very, very costly,"},{"time":88377,"text":"and that means that, outside the clinical trials,"},{"time":91134,"text":"it's just never done. It's never done."}]},{"cues":[{"time":93862,"text":"But what if patients could do this test at home?"},{"time":96939,"text":"Now, that would actually save on a difficult trip to the clinic,"},{"time":99037,"text":"and what if patients could do that test themselves, right?"},{"time":103291,"text":"No expensive staff time required."},{"time":105211,"text":"Takes about $300, by the way,"},{"time":106629,"text":"in the neurologist's clinic to do it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":108622,"text":"So what I want to propose to you as an unconventional way"},{"time":111303,"text":"in which we can try to achieve this,"},{"time":112817,"text":"because, you see, in one sense, at least,"},{"time":114625,"text":"we are all virtuosos like my friend Jan Stripling."}]},{"cues":[{"time":117881,"text":"So here we have a video of the vibrating vocal folds."},{"time":121636,"text":"Now, this is healthy and this is somebody making speech sounds,"},{"time":124865,"text":"and we can think of ourselves as vocal ballet dancers,"},{"time":128329,"text":"because we have to coordinate all of these vocal organs"},{"time":130543,"text":"when we make sounds, and we all actually"},{"time":132838,"text":"have the genes for it. FoxP2, for example."},{"time":135134,"text":"And like ballet, it takes an extraordinary level of training."},{"time":137847,"text":"I mean, just think how long it takes a child to learn to speak."},{"time":140432,"text":"From the sound, we can actually track"},{"time":142814,"text":"the vocal fold position as it vibrates,"},{"time":145095,"text":"and just as the limbs are affected in Parkinson's,"},{"time":147638,"text":"so too are the vocal organs."},{"time":150419,"text":"So on the bottom trace, you can see an example of"},{"time":152299,"text":"irregular vocal fold tremor."},{"time":153997,"text":"We see all the same symptoms."},{"time":155165,"text":"We see vocal tremor, weakness and rigidity."},{"time":158095,"text":"The speech actually becomes quieter and more breathy"},{"time":160199,"text":"after a while, and that's one of the example symptoms of it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":162432,"text":"So these vocal effects can actually be quite subtle,"},{"time":165279,"text":"in some cases, but with any digital microphone,"},{"time":168495,"text":"and using precision voice analysis software"},{"time":171040,"text":"in combination with the latest in machine learning,"},{"time":173449,"text":"which is very advanced by now,"},{"time":175027,"text":"we can now quantify exactly where somebody lies"},{"time":177913,"text":"on a continuum between health and disease"},{"time":180794,"text":"using voice signals alone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":183390,"text":"So these voice-based tests, how do they stack up against"},{"time":185704,"text":"expert clinical tests? We'll, they're both non-invasive."},{"time":187854,"text":"The neurologist's test is non-invasive. They both use existing infrastructure."},{"time":191836,"text":"You don't have to design a whole new set of hospitals to do it."},{"time":194840,"text":"And they're both accurate. Okay, but in addition,"},{"time":197142,"text":"voice-based tests are non-expert."},{"time":200469,"text":"That means they can be self-administered."},{"time":202461,"text":"They're high-speed, take about 30 seconds at most."},{"time":205041,"text":"They're ultra-low cost, and we all know what happens."},{"time":207335,"text":"When something becomes ultra-low cost,"},{"time":209775,"text":"it becomes massively scalable."},{"time":212071,"text":"So here are some amazing goals that I think we can deal with now."},{"time":215746,"text":"We can reduce logistical difficulties with patients."},{"time":218172,"text":"No need to go to the clinic for a routine checkup."},{"time":220484,"text":"We can do high-frequency monitoring to get objective data."},{"time":222804,"text":"We can perform low-cost mass recruitment for clinical trials,"},{"time":226909,"text":"and we can make population-scale screening"},{"time":229024,"text":"feasible for the first time."},{"time":230620,"text":"We have the opportunity to start to search"},{"time":232822,"text":"for the early biomarkers of the disease before it's too late."}]},{"cues":[{"time":236363,"text":"So, taking the first steps towards this today,"},{"time":239121,"text":"we're launching the Parkinson's Voice Initiative."},{"time":241247,"text":"With Aculab and PatientsLikeMe, we're aiming"},{"time":243479,"text":"to record a very large number of voices worldwide"},{"time":245407,"text":"to collect enough data to start to tackle these four goals."},{"time":248547,"text":"We have local numbers accessible to three quarters"},{"time":250247,"text":"of a billion people on the planet."},{"time":251857,"text":"Anyone healthy or with Parkinson's can call in, cheaply,"},{"time":254934,"text":"and leave recordings, a few cents each,"},{"time":257073,"text":"and I'm really happy to announce that we've already hit"},{"time":259263,"text":"six percent of our target just in eight hours."},{"time":262806,"text":"Thank you. (Applause)"},{"time":266557,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":272877,"text":"Tom Rielly: So Max, by taking all these samples of,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":276452,"text":"let's say, 10,000 people,"},{"time":279228,"text":"you'll be able to tell who's healthy and who's not?"},{"time":282082,"text":"What are you going to get out of those samples?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":283767,"text":"Max Little: Yeah. Yeah. So what will happen is that,"},{"time":285597,"text":"during the call you have to indicate whether or not"},{"time":287254,"text":"you have the disease or not, you see. TR: Right."},{"time":288521,"text":"ML: You see, some people may not do it. They may not get through it."},{"time":291028,"text":"But we'll get a very large sample of data that is collected"},{"time":293745,"text":"from all different circumstances, and it's getting it"},{"time":297153,"text":"in different circumstances that matter because then"},{"time":299058,"text":"we are looking at ironing out the confounding factors,"},{"time":302442,"text":"and looking for the actual markers of the disease."}]},{"cues":[{"time":304603,"text":"TR: So you're 86 percent accurate right now?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":307100,"text":"ML: It's much better than that."},{"time":308294,"text":"Actually, my student Thanasis, I have to plug him,"},{"time":310014,"text":"because he's done some fantastic work,"},{"time":311884,"text":"and now he has proved that it works over the mobile telephone network as well,"},{"time":315654,"text":"which enables this project, and we're getting 99 percent accuracy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":319044,"text":"TR: Ninety-nine. Well, that's an improvement."},{"time":320620,"text":"So what that means is that people will be able to â€”"},{"time":322821,"text":"ML: (Laughs)"},{"time":324673,"text":"TR: People will be able to call in from their mobile phones"},{"time":326579,"text":"and do this test, and people with Parkinson's could call in,"},{"time":329651,"text":"record their voice, and then their doctor can check up"},{"time":332521,"text":"on their progress, see where they're doing in this course of the disease."}]},{"cues":[{"time":335202,"text":"ML: Absolutely."}]},{"cues":[{"time":336172,"text":"TR: Thanks so much. Max Little, everybody."}]},{"cues":[{"time":337915,"text":"ML: Thanks, Tom. (Applause)"}]}]}